This paper is primarily focused on face recognition, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The use of probabilistic embeddings also involves machine learning techniques, which could place it in the machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper discusses the evaluation of the proposed method on different benchmarks, which could suggest the use of multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper also mentions the importance of risk-controlled recognition systems, which could place it in the cryptography and security (cs.CR) sub-category.
